Head: with ca. 29 ocelli (
Fig. 64
), arranged in 4 rows (2: 5: 5: 7).

Distribution and habitat:
This species has a coastal distribution from Torbay to Albany along the south coast of 
Western Australia
(
Fig. 5
). Specimens can be found in mixed karri (

Eucalyptus diversicolor

) forest, mixed jarrah (

E. marginata

), blackbutt (

E. patens

) and marri (

Corymbia calophylla

) open woodland, and on granite outcrops. Collections of this species were from under rotting logs, under bark of fallen logs, under bark of live karri (

Eucalyptus diversicolor

) trees, and under leaf litter.
